### 3. Storybook configuration to exclude default values

You can also add a global configuration to your .storybook/preview.js file to exclude default values from the code snippet:

```js
// .storybook/preview.js
export const parameters = {
  actions: { argTypesRegex: "^on[A-Z].*" },
  controls: {
    matchers: {
      color: /(background|color)$/i,
      date: /Date$/,
    },
  },
  docs: {
    source: {
      // Exclude default values from the code snippet
      excludeDecorators: true,
      transformSource: (source, storyContext) => {
        // This will show only the props that differ from defaults
        // You might need to customize this further
        return source
          .replace(/\s+icon={null}/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+iconPosition="end"/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+dataSize="medium"/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+disabled={false}/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+loading={false}/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+color=""/g, '')
          .replace(/\s+theme="light"/g, '');
      },
    },
  },
};
```

### Key Improvements

1. **Component Refactoring**: The Button component now only applies props that have meaningful values
2. **Story Configuration**: Each story only specifies props that differ from defaults
3. **Source Transformation**: Added a global config to remove default props from code snippets
4. **Conditional Controls**: Using Storybook's conditional controls feature to only show relevant controls (like iconPosition only if icon exists)

These changes will ensure that the "show code" part of Storybook only displays properties that are actually being used and have non-default values. This makes the example code cleaner and more representative of how the component would actually be used in real applications.
